# AgriApp — Project Constitution (Source of Truth)

This file governs **all future code generation** for this repository. When in doubt, follow these rules over ad-hoc patterns.

**No frontend entity duplication:** **`AgriApp.Web` MUST NOT** recreate database entities or parallel domain types. Use **`AgriApp.Core.Entities`** and **`AgriApp.Core.Enums`** only (project reference).

---

## 1. Core tech stack and architecture

### Backend

- **.NET 8**, **Clean Architecture**: **AgriApp.Core**, **AgriApp.Application**, **AgriApp.Infrastructure**, **AgriApp.Api**.
- **EF Core** for persistence (Infrastructure).
- **JWT** authentication on the API (`Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer`).

### Frontend

- **Blazor WebAssembly**, **standalone PWA** (service worker / SW manifest in `AgriApp.Web`).
- **MudBlazor** for UI components.
- **Blazored.LocalStorage** for client-side storage.
- **JWT**: Bearer token attached via a dedicated HTTP message handler; `AuthenticationStateProvider` for auth state.

### Layering (non-negotiable)

- **Core**: entities, enums, domain rules—no UI or infrastructure dependencies.
- **Application**: use cases, interfaces—no concrete EF or HTTP clients.
- **Infrastructure**: EF Core, external integrations.
- **Api**: HTTP surface, auth wiring, mapping to application layer.
- **Web**: Blazor UI, API client services, view models—references **Core** for **`Entities`** / **`Enums`** only; never duplicate domain entities in the Web project.

---

## 2. The “No-ID” UI rule (mandatory)

### Relational lookups (`*Id` properties)

Whenever a **DTO or entity property name ends with `Id`** (e.g. `EquipmentId`, `CustomerId`, `VendorId`, `CenterId`):

- **Do not** render a **`MudTextField`** (or any free-text input) for that value.
- **Do** inject the **`I…Service`** that loads the related list.
- **Do** load options in **`OnInitializedAsync`** (or equivalent lifecycle).
- **Do** render a **searchable `MudAutocomplete`** or **`MudSelect`** that:
  - **displays** the related entity’s human-readable field (typically **Name**), and
  - **binds** the model to the **ID** (the `*Id` property).

### Cancel / Close in dialogs

All **“Cancel”** or **“Close”** buttons **inside `MudDialog` / dialog content** **MUST** use:

`ButtonType="ButtonType.Button"`

so they **never** submit a parent **`EditForm`** by accident.

### Global user feedback for API errors

Use **`ISnackbar`** with **`Severity.Error`** for backend/API failures so users never see raw exceptions or silent failures.

---

## 3. Logging and exception handling standards

### Service implementations (all tiers that perform I/O)

- Inject **`ILogger<T>`** into **every service implementation** (Application handlers, Infrastructure services, **`AgriApp.Web.Services` HTTP clients**, etc.).
- Wrap **every external API call** and **every database operation** in **`try` / `catch`**.
- **Log** the **full exception** (use structured logging where the codebase already does).
- **Re-throw** a **descriptive, user-friendly `ApplicationException`** (or preserve inner exception) so callers can surface a safe message—**do not** swallow errors without logging.

### UI layer (Razor components)

- Wrap **all service calls** (async API operations triggered from the UI) in **`try` / `catch`**.
- On failure: **`ISnackbar.Add(message, Severity.Error)`** (or equivalent Mud API) with a **clear, non-sensitive** message.
- **Never** rely on silent failure or uncaught exceptions that only appear in the browser console for expected error paths.

### Web API HTTP clients

- All HTTP calls from **`AgriApp.Web`** go through **interfaces** under **`AgriApp.Web.Services`**, using the named **`HttpClient` `"AgriApi"`** (`IHttpClientFactory`).

---

## 4. Testing standards

### Framework (target for new work)

- **xUnit**, **Moq**, **FluentAssertions**.

### Project layout (mirror architecture)

Create and maintain test assemblies aligned with layers:

- **`AgriApp.UnitTests.Core`**
- **`AgriApp.UnitTests.Application`**
- **`AgriApp.UnitTests.Web`**

Place tests next to the code they validate; namespaces should reflect the system under test.

### Coverage expectations

For **every new business-logic service** (or equivalent application service):

- Add at least one **happy path** test.
- Add at least one **failure case** test (e.g. validation failure, conflict, or **capacity / double-booking** rules where applicable).

### Legacy note

The repository may still contain **`AgriApp.Application.Tests`** using **MSTest**. **Do not add new MSTest tests**; prefer **xUnit + Moq + FluentAssertions** for new tests and migrate legacy projects when you touch them.

---

## 5. Clean code constraints

### C#

- Prefer **C# 12** features where they improve clarity: **primary constructors**, **collection expressions** (`[]`), etc., when consistent with existing files in the same area.

### DTOs and view models

- All **frontend Request/Response** (and similar UI-specific) models **MUST** live in **`src/AgriApp.Web/Services/ViewModels.cs`** as **`record`** types.
- **Do not** add UI-specific DTOs to **AgriApp.Core**.
- **Do not** introduce a **`Models`** folder in **Web** for these; keep **`ViewModels.cs`** as the single home unless the team explicitly splits it later with the same rule.

### Namespaces

Follow established roots:

- **`AgriApp.Web.Services`**, **`AgriApp.Web.Pages`**, **`AgriApp.Web.Layout`**, **`AgriApp.Web.Shared`**, **`AgriApp.Web.Security`**, etc.

### API client discipline

- No raw **`HttpClient`** usage scattered in `.razor` files—use injected **`I…Service`** implementations that encapsulate **`"AgriApi"`**.

---

## 6. Quick checklist (before merging)

- [ ] No `MudTextField` for `*Id` lookup fields—use **`MudAutocomplete`** / **`MudSelect`** with loaded options.
- [ ] Dialog Cancel/Close: **`ButtonType="ButtonType.Button"`**.
- [ ] Services: **`ILogger<T>`**, **try/catch** on I/O, logged exceptions.
- [ ] Razor: **try/catch** on service calls + **`ISnackbar`** on error.
- [ ] New DTOs: **`ViewModels.cs`** **`record`** types only.
- [ ] New logic: tests per **§4** (xUnit / Moq / FluentAssertions).
